<figureCitation box="[966,1027,1768,1790]" captionStart="FIGURES 1" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1510,1534]" captionTargetBox="[174,1412,360,1473]" captionTargetId="figure-99@4.[166,1422,345,1486]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1─8. Domahovana gen. nov. habitus of type specimens, dorsal and lateral view respectively. 1─2 Domahovana icamiabas sp. nov. male holotype (INPA). 3─4 Domahovana icamiabas sp. nov. female paratype (INPA). 5─6 Domahovana mani sp. nov. male holotype (INPA). 7─8 Domahovana mani sp. nov. female paratype (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877229" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877229/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 3); aedeagus with two pairs of atrial processes, one dorsal and another ventral (Figs 22–23)................................ 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1114,1436,1796,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya, 2022" authorityName="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2022" box="[1114,1354,1796,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Domahovana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="icamiabas" status="sp. nov.">
