<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,1797,1818]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="171">- Mesonotum with two dark maculae adjacent to posterior margin of pronotum (Figs 7, 9, 13); aedeagus without dorsal atrial pair of processes (Figs 42–43, 62–63, 83–84).................................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
2 Mesonotum with pair of small and narrow dark maculae adjacent to posterior margin of pronotum (Figs 5, 7); aedeagus atrium with pair of ventral processes, shaft without tegumentary teeth and paired ventral lamellae expanded laterally at median third (Figs 42–43)................................................................... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1163,1436,1943,1965]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya, 2022" authorityName="Silva &amp; Gonçalves &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2022" box="[1163,1354,1943,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Domahovana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mani" status="sp. nov.">
