<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1360,1436,1944,1965]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
<keyLead pageId="13" pageNumber="171">
- Mesonotum with pair of large dark maculae adjacent to posterior margin of pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1073,1136,1973,1995]" captionStart="FIGURES 9" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1884,1908]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,462,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-150@5.[151,1435,453,1861]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9─14. Domahovana gen. nov. habitus of type specimens, dorsal and lateral view respectively. 9─10 Domahovana naia sp. nov. male holotype (INPA). 11─12 Domahovana naia sp. nov. female paratype (INPA). 13─14 Domahovana yamurikuma sp. nov. male holotype (INPA)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877233/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="171">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 11, 13); aedeagus atrium with single ventral process, shaft with several tegumentary teeth and without ventral lamellae (Figs 62–63, 83–84)............ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
